entry_logic_summary: Enter when price closes below lower Bollinger Band (20,2). Exit when price closes above middle band
primary_exit_logic: Close when price closes above middle band
implementation_notes: Simple and well-known indicator. Multiple entry signals over time. Consider using position size = volatility-adjusted.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price is below SMA(50) and crosses above SMA(10). Close SMA(10) < SMA(50)
implementation_notes: Double SMA strategy. Frequent signals with clear logic. Should work well with entry+exit optimization.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when SAR flips from above price to below price (bullish signal). Exit when SAR flips back
primary_exit_logic: Exit when SAR flips from below to above price
implementation_notes: Tracks trends with trailing stop behavior. May give late entries. Works best in trending markets.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when Supertrend flips bullish (green). Exit when it flips bearish
implementation_notes: ATR-based trend indicator. Similar to SAR but with customizable sensitivity via multiplier.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when MOM(10) crosses above 0. Exit when MOM(10) crosses below 0
implementation_notes: Rate-of-change indicator. May be choppy in sideways markets. Best during trending periods.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when VWAP-weighted MACD crosses above signal. Exit when it crosses below
primary_exit_logic: Exit when MACD crosses below signal line
implementation_notes: Combines volume and momentum. Requires volume data. More responsive to volume-driven moves.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when ATR(14) increases above threshold and price breaks high. Exit when ATR falls
primary_exit_logic: Exit when ATR falls below threshold
implementation_notes: Volatility expansion strategy. Look for breakouts during high volatility. May give false signals in chop.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when CMO(14) crosses above -50 (bullish). Exit when crosses below 50
implementation_notes: Chande Momentum Oscillator. Similar to RSI but using different math. May give earlier signals.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when CRSI < 10 (extreme oversold). Exit when CRSI > 75
implementation_notes: Uses 3 components: RSI(3)
column16: up/down streak. Very responsive. May give many signals.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when psychological line (% up days in N periods) < 25%. Exit when > 75%
implementation_notes: Tracks percentage of up days. Simple but effective mean reversion indicator.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when WT crosses above oversold level (-60). Exit when crosses below overbought (53)
implementation_notes: Oscillator based on momentum and EMA. Good for finding extremes. Can lag in fast markets.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when KST crosses above signal line. Exit when crosses below
primary_exit_logic: Exit when KST crosses below signal
key_parameters: kst_roc1: 10, kst_roc2: 15, kst_roc3: 20, kst_roc4: 30, kst_sma1: 10, kst_sma2: 10, kst_sma3: 10, kst_sma4: 15, kst_signal: 9
implementation_notes: Complex momentum indicator using 4 ROC periods. Smoothed and summed. Very comprehensive.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when volume > 1.5x average and price up. Exit when volume < average
implementation_notes: Volume confirmation strategy. Simple volume spike detection. Needs volume data.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when PVT crosses above SMA(PVT, 10). Exit when crosses below
primary_exit_logic: Exit when PVT crosses below SMA
implementation_notes: Cumulative volume indicator weighted by price change. Like OBV but with price % change.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price breaks above upper channel (highest high N bars). Exit when breaks below lower
primary_exit_logic: Exit when price breaks below lower channel
implementation_notes: Donchian Channel breakout. Classic breakout strategy. May whipsaw in range-bound markets.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price touches lower envelope (SMA ± X%). Exit at middle band
implementation_notes: Like Bollinger Bands but uses fixed % instead of standard deviation. Simpler calculation.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when fast MA(10) crosses above slow MA(50). Exit on opposite cross
primary_exit_logic: Exit when fast MA crosses below slow MA
implementation_notes: Classic dual moving average crossover. Many parameters to optimize. Well-studied approach.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when fast(5) > medium(10) > slow(20), confirming trend. Exit when order breaks
implementation_notes: Three moving averages for stronger trend confirmation. More conservative entries.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when MACD crosses above signal line. Exit when crosses below
primary_exit_logic: Exit when MACD crosses below signal
implementation_notes: Most popular momentum indicator. Many false signals in ranging markets.

entry_logic_summary: Enter on SAR flip to bullish. Exit on flip to bearish
primary_exit_logic: Exit on SAR flip to bearish
implementation_notes: Duplicate of #3. Can remove or modify to test different parameters.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when RSI(2) < 10. Exit when RSI(2) > 65
implementation_notes: Very short-term RSI. Larry Connors style. Gives frequent signals. Works well on liquid instruments.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price breaks above recent swing high with volume confirmation. Exit at next resistance
primary_exit_logic: Exit at resistance or fixed target
implementation_notes: Identifies swing highs/lows. Breakout with volume. Requires swing detection logic.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when gap > 1% at open, expecting reversion. Exit when gap 50% filled
implementation_notes: Needs intraday or daily open/close data. Simple gap detection and mean reversion trade.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price deviates >2 std devs from VWAP. Exit at VWAP
primary_exit_logic: Exit when price returns to VWAP
implementation_notes: Requires intraday data and volume. VWAP as anchor. Standard deviation bands for entry.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price breaks above/below first 30-min range. Exit at close or stop
implementation_notes: Classic intraday strategy. Needs 15-min or better data. Simple logic for implementation.

entry_logic_summary: Enter at pivot support/resistance levels. Exit at opposite level or middle
primary_exit_logic: Exit at opposite pivot or midpoint
implementation_notes: Daily pivots from prior day high/low/close. Standard formulas. Requires daily OHLC.

entry_logic_summary: Enter after 3 consecutive bars down, then breakout above. Exit after X bars
implementation_notes: Pattern recognition. 3 down bars = setup
column15: breakout bar = entry. Simple state machine.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price makes new high AND volume > average. Exit when volume dries up
implementation_notes: Combines price action with volume. Needs volume data. Filters weak breakouts.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when z-score(TLT-ES spread) > 2. Exit when z-score returns to 0
implementation_notes: Requires both ES and TLT data. Spread calculation and z-score. Cointegration testing recommended.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when price deviates from Kalman predicted price. Exit at convergence
primary_exit_logic: Exit when within 0.5 std dev of prediction
implementation_notes: Requires Kalman filter implementation. Advanced math. Adaptive to regime changes.

entry_logic_summary: Model price as OU process, enter when far from mean-reversion level. Exit at mean
primary_exit_logic: Exit when price within 0.3 std dev of mean
implementation_notes: Stochastic process modeling. Half-life calculation. Requires parameter estimation.

entry_logic_summary: Detect regime changes using HMM or variance filters. Adjust strategy based on regime
implementation_notes: Hidden Markov Model or variance ratio tests. Switches between mean reversion and trend following.

entry_logic_summary: Find cointegrated pairs, enter when spread exceeds threshold. Exit at spread mean
primary_exit_logic: Exit when spread returns to mean
implementation_notes: Requires cointegration testing (ADF/Johansen). Multi-instrument. Hedge ratio calculation.

entry_logic_summary: Enter on 1-min or tick imbalances, quick mean reversion trades. Exit within minutes
primary_exit_logic: Exit after 5 minutes or mean reversion
implementation_notes: Needs tick or 1-min data. Very short holding period. Sensitive to transaction costs.

entry_logic_summary: Fit linear regression to price, enter on breakout from channel. Exit on opposite signal
primary_exit_logic: Exit when price crosses opposite channel
implementation_notes: Rolling linear regression. Channel = regression line ± std dev. Breakout strategy.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when RSI(2) < 5 AND price > SMA(200). Exit when RSI(2) > 70
implementation_notes: Classic Connors setup. Long-term trend filter + short-term mean reversion. Very systematic.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when 7-day price % rank < 5%. Exit when 7-day % rank > 95%
implementation_notes: Percentile rank over 7 days. Pure mean reversion on extremes. No indicators needed.

entry_logic_summary: Enter RSI(2) < 10, close > MA(200), 2 consecutive down days. Exit RSI(2) > 65
implementation_notes: Multiple filters: trend
column16: and streak. More selective than simple RSI(2).

entry_logic_summary: Sum RSI(2) over 2 days. Enter when sum < 25. Exit when today's RSI(2) > 60
implementation_notes: Adds up RSI over multiple days for more extreme signals. Still mean reversion focused.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when close < lowest low of previous 5 bars, indicating potential oversold reversal
primary_exit_logic: Exit when close > high[1] showing price strength
implementation_notes: Simple mean reversion on 5-bar lows. Works on any timeframe. High frequency of signals in volatile markets. Best for stocks/ETFs/futures.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when close < lowest low of previous 3 bars, with optional EMA filter
primary_exit_logic: Exit when close > highest high of previous 7 bars
implementation_notes: Faster signals than 5-bar low. Asymmetric entry/exit windows (3 bars in, 7 bars out). Works on any timeframe from intraday to daily.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when: 1) previous bar bearish, 2) current open < prior low (gap down), 3) current close > open (bullish reversal)
primary_exit_logic: Exit when close > highest high of previous 7 bars
implementation_notes: Capitalizes on gap down exhaustion. Requires true gap below prior low. Best on timeframes with gaps (daily, 1HR+). Works in high volatility.

strategy_name: Turn of the Month Strategy on Steroids
entry_logic_summary: Enter when day of month >= threshold (default 25) AND close < close[1], exploiting turn-of-month effect
implementation_notes: Exploits calendar anomaly - stocks tend to rise end of month. Mean reversion entry with RSI exit. Requires daily bars for calendar tracking.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when close < lower Bollinger Band (2σ) AND IBS indicates oversold conditions
implementation_notes: Combines volatility (BB) with intrabar strength (IBS) for double confirmation. Exits on IBS overbought. Best in mean-reverting markets. Timeframe agnostic.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when IBS < threshold (default 0.2), meaning close near bar's low
implementation_notes: Pure IBS mean reversion. IBS = (close-low)/(high-low). Simple calculation, no warmup needed. Best in ranging markets. Works on any timeframe.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when close < reference close (N bars ago) for at least N consecutive bars, indicating sustained bearish move
primary_exit_logic: Exit when close > high[1] confirming reversal
implementation_notes: Momentum exhaustion strategy. Requires sustained selling before entry. Reference close lookback customizable. Works on any timeframe from intraday to daily.

entry_logic_summary: Enter after N consecutive bars where close[i] < close[i-1] (default 3), identifying momentum exhaustion
implementation_notes: Simple consecutive down bar counter. More flexible than 4-bar momentum. Timeframe agnostic. Best in volatile markets with frequent swings.

strategy_name: Consecutive Bars Above/Below EMA Buy the Dip Strategy
entry_logic_summary: Enter when close remains below selected MA (SMA or EMA) for N consecutive bars (default 3), identifying dip
implementation_notes: MA-based dip buying. Customizable MA type and length. Counts consecutive bars below MA. Works on any timeframe when price oscillates around short-term MA.

strategy_name: Average High-Low Range + IBS Reversal Strategy
entry_logic_summary: Enter when: 1) close below (upper - 2.5×avg_HL_range) for N bars (default 2), 2) IBS < threshold (default 0.2)
implementation_notes: Combines volatility measure (avg high-low range) with IBS. Avg_HL = SMA(high-low, 20). Identifies extreme deviations. Works on any timeframe.

entry_logic_summary: Enter after N consecutive down closes (default 3), with optional 200 EMA filter
primary_exit_logic: Exit after N consecutive up closes (default 3)
implementation_notes: Symmetric entry/exit logic. Simple consecutive close counter. Optional trend filter improves reliability. Works on any timeframe. Best in oscillating/volatile markets. NOT optimized.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when consecutive bars of close < low[1] reaches threshold (default 3), indicating overextended bearish move
implementation_notes: Contrarian strategy for overextended bearish moves. Counts aggressive down bars where each close breaks prior low. Works on any timeframe from intraday to daily.

strategy_name: ATR Buy the Dip Mean Reversion
entry_logic_summary: Enter when close < smoothed ATR lower trigger (close - ATR×multiplier smoothed), indicating oversold
implementation_notes: ATR-based oversold detection. Dynamic lower threshold = SMA(close - ATR×mult, smooth_period). Enters on extreme dips below volatility-adjusted level. Timeframe agnostic.

entry_logic_summary: Enter when IBS <= 0.1 (close near bar's low), indicating extreme oversold
implementation_notes: More extreme version of IBS strategy #46. Uses lower threshold (0.1 vs 0.2) for fewer but higher-conviction signals. Works on any timeframe for stocks/ETFs/futures.

strategy_name: 10 Bar High Breakout with Low IBS
entry_logic_summary: Enter when: 1) high > highest(high, 10) breaking out to new high, 2) low IBS (default <= 0.15) for pullback confirmation
implementation_notes: Breakout strategy with pullback confirmation. New 10-bar high with low IBS suggests consolidation before breakout. Combines momentum with mean reversion filter. Works on any timeframe.
